{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:psalms.105",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 105,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 105 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:1",
      "text": "Give thanks to Yahweh! Call on his name! Make his doings known among the peoples.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:2",
      "text": "Sing to him, sing praises to him! Tell of all his marvelous works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:3",
      "text": "Glory in his holy name. Let the heart of those who seek Yahweh rejoice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:4",
      "text": "Seek Yahweh and his strength. Seek his face forever more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:5",
      "text": "Remember his marvelous works that he has done: his wonders, and the judgments of his mouth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:6",
      "text": "you offspring of Abraham, his servant, you children of Jacob, his chosen ones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:7",
      "text": "He is Yahweh, our God. His judgments are in all the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:8",
      "text": "He has remembered his covenant forever, the word which he commanded to a thousand generations,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:9",
      "text": "the covenant which he made with Abraham, his oath to Isaac,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:10",
      "text": "and confirmed it to Jacob for a statute; to Israel for an everlasting covenant,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:11",
      "text": "saying, “ To you I will give the land of Canaan, the lot of your inheritance,”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:12",
      "text": "when they were but a few men in number, yes, very few, and foreigners in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:13",
      "text": "They went about from nation to nation, from one kingdom to another people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:14",
      "text": "He allowed no one to do them wrong. Yes, he reproved kings for their sakes,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:15",
      "text": "“Don’t touch my anointed ones! Do my prophets no harm!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:16",
      "text": "He called for a famine on the land. He destroyed the food supplies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:17",
      "text": "He sent a man before them. Joseph was sold for a slave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:18",
      "text": "They bruised his feet with shackles. His neck was locked in irons,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:19",
      "text": "until the time that his word happened, and Yahweh ’s word proved him true.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:20",
      "text": "The king sent and freed him, even the ruler of peoples, and let him go free.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:21",
      "text": "He made him lord of his house, and ruler of all of his possessions,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:22",
      "text": "to discipline his princes at his pleasure, and to teach his elders wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:23",
      "text": "Israel also came into Egypt. Jacob lived in the land of Ham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:24",
      "text": "He increased his people greatly, and made them stronger than their adversaries.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:25",
      "text": "He turned their heart to hate his people, to conspire against his servants.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:26",
      "text": "He sent Moses, his servant, and Aaron, whom he had chosen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:27",
      "text": "They performed miracles among them, and wonders in the land of Ham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:28",
      "text": "He sent darkness, and made it dark. They didn’t rebel against his words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:29",
      "text": "He turned their waters into blood, and killed their fish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:30",
      "text": "Their land swarmed with frogs, even in the rooms of their kings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:31",
      "text": "He spoke, and swarms of flies came, and lice in all their borders.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:32",
      "text": "He gave them hail for rain, with lightning in their land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:33",
      "text": "He struck their vines and also their fig trees, and shattered the trees of their country.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:34",
      "text": "He spoke, and the locusts came with the grasshoppers, without number.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:35",
      "text": "They ate up every plant in their land, and ate up the fruit of their ground.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:36",
      "text": "He struck also all the firstborn in their land, the first fruits of all their manhood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.37",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:37",
      "text": "He brought them out with silver and gold. There was not one feeble person among his tribes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.38",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:38",
      "text": "Egypt was glad when they departed, for the fear of them had fallen on them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.39",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:39",
      "text": "He spread a cloud for a covering, fire to give light in the night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.40",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:40",
      "text": "They asked, and he brought quails, and satisfied them with the bread of the sky.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.41",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:41",
      "text": "He opened the rock, and waters gushed out. They ran as a river in the dry places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.42",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:42",
      "text": "For he remembered his holy word, and Abraham, his servant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.43",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:43",
      "text": "He brought his people out with joy, his chosen with singing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.44",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:44",
      "text": "He gave them the lands of the nations. They took the labor of the peoples in possession,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.105.45",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:45",
      "text": "that they might keep his statutes, and observe his laws. Praise Yah!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
